# Regression: `from gen::series(...)` used to panic (unreachable/unimplemented
# in ExpressionCompiler::compile) instead of producing a diagnostic. The
# generator-call syntax `name { args }` is not recognized with parens, so the
# parser falls back to treating `gen::series` as a shape source and the
# trailing `(1, 3)` as a call on top of it; compiling that as a scalar
# expression must fail cleanly, not crash the process.

!query 'from gen::series(1, 3)'
---
> Error AST_009
>   unsupported query syntax: From
>
> LOCATION
>   line 1, column 1
>
> RQL
>   1 │ from gen::series(1, 3)
>     │ ~~~~
>     │
>     │ not supported in this context
>
> HELP
>   This syntax is not yet supported or may be invalid in this context
>
